1
00:00:20,640 --> 00:00:21,880
(In ancient times,)

2
00:00:21,880 --> 00:00:25,760
(a meteorite split into nine fragments
that fell to Earth.)

3
00:00:29,600 --> 00:00:31,039
(Where meteorites fell,)

4
00:00:31,039 --> 00:00:33,359
(all lifeforms
were contaminated by radiation,)

5
00:00:33,359 --> 00:00:35,800
(transforming
into entirely new lifeforms.)

6
00:00:38,440 --> 00:00:40,079
(In isolated environments,)

7
00:00:40,079 --> 00:00:42,159
(they formed self-contained ecosystems.)

8
00:00:42,280 --> 00:00:43,320
(Humanity)

9
00:00:43,399 --> 00:00:46,320
(couldn't survive
within these ecological chains.)

10
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:51,920
(Ancient people considered this
divine revelation.)

11
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:55,600
(They constructed temples
to worship the meteorites.)

12
00:00:55,799 --> 00:00:57,520
(But the meteorites' power)

13
00:00:57,520 --> 00:00:59,399
(was too extraordinary.)

14
00:00:59,399 --> 00:01:01,240
(Those who obtained them)

15
00:01:01,320 --> 00:01:03,880
(sought to keep their existence secret.)

16
00:01:04,240 --> 00:01:06,079
(Thus, they devised methods)

17
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:08,560
(to conceal the temples.)

18
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:11,799
(Yet these ecosystems)

19
00:01:11,960 --> 00:01:14,359
(still exist worldwide,)

20
00:01:14,760 --> 00:01:17,760
(awaiting new waves
of greedy opportunists)

21
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:20,560
(and unsuspecting trespassers.)

22
00:01:30,228 --> 00:01:34,656
(Dart Summit, Hezhou, 1920s)

23
00:01:44,627 --> 00:01:45,467
Well.

24
00:01:46,239 --> 00:01:47,280
Now we're

25
00:01:48,079 --> 00:01:49,599
in deep trouble.

26
00:01:50,719 --> 00:01:52,560
(Old Smoker)
The soil's bloody.

27
00:01:53,719 --> 00:01:56,000
(Young Wu Laogou)
There's a blood corpse down there.

28
00:01:56,959 --> 00:01:58,359
If we mess this up,

29
00:01:58,640 --> 00:02:00,040
everything we've got

30
00:02:00,599 --> 00:02:02,319
will get buried below.

31
00:02:03,319 --> 00:02:05,079
Yes or no? Just one word.

32
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:07,120
(Er Yazi)
Stop this nonsense.

33
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,560
(Beardy)
Respect your great-grandpa!

34
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:09,680
When he was tomb raiding,

35
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:10,799
you were still a fetus.

36
00:02:10,799 --> 00:02:12,000
I wasn't wrong.

37
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:13,560
Our ancestors said

38
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:15,239
blood corpses bring good fortune.

39
00:02:17,080 --> 00:02:18,319
Want to lose your head?

40
00:02:20,639 --> 00:02:21,919
Your second great-uncle

41
00:02:21,919 --> 00:02:24,439
dug up one of these
by South River earlier.

42
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:27,319
He's still crazy to this day.

43
00:02:27,719 --> 00:02:30,039
No idea what cursed him.

44
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:35,199
Down or not? Decide now.

45
00:02:35,599 --> 00:02:37,000
No more excuses.

46
00:02:37,439 --> 00:02:38,599
When

47
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:40,919
the hole's ready,

48
00:02:40,919 --> 00:02:42,199
I'll go first.

49
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:45,639
Er Yazi, bring up the rear
with the drag hoe.

50
00:02:48,520 --> 00:02:49,439
San Yazi,

51
00:02:50,639 --> 00:02:52,520
stay up here.

52
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:56,360
If we all go down,
there's no time to retreat.

53
00:02:56,680 --> 00:03:00,120
Hold the drag hoe's tail up here.

54
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:02,680
When we shout from below,

55
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:04,759
pull it out immediately.

56
00:03:04,960 --> 00:03:06,000
I don't want to stay.

57
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:06,840
I'm going down too.

58
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,159
I'll dig right now.

59
00:03:08,639 --> 00:03:10,639
You brat! Are you testing my patience?

60
00:03:10,639 --> 00:03:11,759
Got a death wish?

61
00:03:18,879 --> 00:03:19,719
Enough!

62
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:25,280
Boys, gear up.

63
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,360
Let's work.

64
00:03:33,439 --> 00:03:36,319
I'll find you a golden blade down there.

65
00:03:37,479 --> 00:03:38,319
Be good.

66
00:03:40,479 --> 00:03:41,319
It's dangerous.

67
00:04:18,439 --> 00:04:19,400
Er Yazi,

68
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:21,360
are you done?

69
00:04:22,319 --> 00:04:23,400
Quiet.

70
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:26,600
Stay there and hold the rope tight.

71
00:04:33,399 --> 00:04:35,360
Move quicker.

72
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:38,079
Try harder.

73
00:04:38,079 --> 00:04:39,199
Quieter!

74
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:42,279
There is movement.

75
00:04:56,279 --> 00:04:58,000
San Yazi!

76
00:04:58,879 --> 00:04:59,719
Pull!

77
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:18,480
Poison!

78
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:19,519
It's poison!

79
00:05:22,439 --> 00:05:23,560
San Yazi,

80
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:24,879
run!

81
00:05:59,399 --> 00:06:00,240
Er Yazi?

82
00:07:56,755 --> 00:07:59,723
(Ancient silk manuscript)

83
00:08:34,228 --> 00:08:39,051
(Wu Laogou's Notes)

84
00:08:41,799 --> 00:08:42,840
(My name is Wu Xie.)

85
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:44,879
(The San Yazi from the story)

86
00:08:44,879 --> 00:08:46,159
(was my grandfather.)

87
00:08:46,639 --> 00:08:48,799
(He was a tomb raider in Hezhou.)

88
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:50,840
(He got his education after 1949)

89
00:08:50,879 --> 00:08:52,559
(and recognized his past mistakes.)

90
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:56,919
(Wu Xie)
(To start anew,)

91
00:08:56,919 --> 00:08:58,120
(he gave away his wealth,)

92
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,279
(married into Hangzhou,)

93
00:08:59,519 --> 00:09:00,759
(and opened an antique shop.)

94
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:08,320
(My grandfather never told me)

95
00:09:09,679 --> 00:09:11,519
(how he survived back then.)

96
00:09:12,279 --> 00:09:13,840
(But that blood corpse he mentioned)

97
00:09:14,399 --> 00:09:16,080
(was his poisoned second brother.)

98
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,679
(And the bizarre experiences)

99
00:09:19,279 --> 00:09:20,840
(in his notes made me)

100
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:22,000
(believe)

101
00:09:22,879 --> 00:09:25,440
(that there must be sides of him
I've never seen.)

102
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:29,240
Xie,

103
00:09:29,639 --> 00:09:30,559
remember this.

104
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:33,919
The clever ones always claim
with confidence,

105
00:09:33,919 --> 00:09:35,720
"See beyond mountains

106
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:37,120
and see beyond waters."

107
00:09:37,600 --> 00:09:38,480
But

108
00:09:38,879 --> 00:09:40,480
the truly remarkable people

109
00:09:40,759 --> 00:09:43,360
see mountains as mountains

110
00:09:43,639 --> 00:09:45,759
and water as water.

111
00:09:48,799 --> 00:09:49,639
Fifth Master.

112
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:57,600
Alright.

113
00:09:57,799 --> 00:09:59,759
Be careful.

114
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,120
How many times have I told you?

115
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:12,120
The things you did in the past

116
00:10:12,799 --> 00:10:14,200
will become responsibilities

117
00:10:14,559 --> 00:10:15,919
you'll carry in the days to come.

118
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:20,560
Just go.

119
00:10:20,759 --> 00:10:22,120
I'll handle this matter.

120
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:23,440
Okay.

121
00:10:34,519 --> 00:10:35,440
Xie.

122
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,840
(My grandfather spent his entire life)

123
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:45,120
(trying to resolve
the karmic consequences.)

124
00:10:46,559 --> 00:10:48,600
(The accounts in this notebook
seem thrilling,)

125
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:51,759
(but they were shackles
to my grandfather)

126
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:55,440
(that bound him until his dying day.)

127
00:12:24,340 --> 00:12:28,576
=Time Raiders=

128
00:12:28,576 --> 00:12:31,520
=Episode 1=

129
00:12:37,716 --> 00:12:38,976
(Wushanju)

130
00:12:41,679 --> 00:12:43,159
(As you can see,)

131
00:12:43,639 --> 00:12:44,600
(to this day,)

132
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:46,679
(I'm just a small antique shop owner.)

133
00:12:47,559 --> 00:12:48,679
(Since childhood,)

134
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:49,800
(I've rarely)

135
00:12:50,159 --> 00:12:51,720
(ventured beyond my doorstep.)

136
00:12:52,759 --> 00:12:54,639
(When will my legendary life)

137
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:56,960
(finally begin?)

138
00:13:24,692 --> 00:13:28,800
(Jin Wantang, 'Gold Tooth')

139
00:13:30,759 --> 00:13:33,639
Do you accept rubbings here?

140
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:36,280
We do.

141
00:13:36,559 --> 00:13:37,559
Prices aren't high.

142
00:13:41,559 --> 00:13:43,279
Let me ask you something.

143
00:13:43,919 --> 00:13:46,519
Do you have rubbings
of an ancient silk manuscript?

144
00:13:47,039 --> 00:13:48,759
I mean the one from decades ago

145
00:13:48,759 --> 00:13:50,559
that some tomb raiders
from Hezhou retrieved

146
00:13:50,559 --> 00:13:53,080
but later got swindled out of.

147
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,039
You just said it was swindled out of.

148
00:13:58,039 --> 00:13:59,559
How would I have it?

149
00:13:59,799 --> 00:14:02,080
Besides, you should hunt for rubbings
at the market.

150
00:14:03,279 --> 00:14:04,799
No one looks for a specific scroll.

151
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:09,240
I heard you have connections.

152
00:14:12,960 --> 00:14:14,879
Lao Yang sent me.

153
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,120
I know the rules.

154
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:23,360
This is the token.

155
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:34,080
Fine, let's say Lao Yang sent you.

156
00:14:34,879 --> 00:14:35,719
What do you want?

157
00:14:36,360 --> 00:14:37,559
I'm not here

158
00:14:37,559 --> 00:14:38,960
to see you.

159
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:41,840
I came to meet your grandfather.

160
00:14:42,279 --> 00:14:45,159
Didn't he once dig for treasures?

161
00:14:47,159 --> 00:14:48,120
What's your game?

162
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:49,879
No games.

163
00:14:50,279 --> 00:14:52,399
I just want to ask

164
00:14:52,919 --> 00:14:54,879
if your grandfather has kept

165
00:14:54,879 --> 00:14:56,440
one or two rubbings

166
00:14:56,440 --> 00:14:58,000
of the silk manuscript

167
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,279
retrieved from Dart Summit in Hezhou.

168
00:15:00,399 --> 00:15:01,239
Wang Meng,

169
00:15:01,559 --> 00:15:02,399
see him out.

170
00:15:03,759 --> 00:15:04,919
What's this about?

171
00:15:04,919 --> 00:15:05,799
We had a good chat.

172
00:15:05,799 --> 00:15:07,200
Why are you throwing me out?

173
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,040
Please leave now.

174
00:15:09,399 --> 00:15:11,320
At least check out what I brought.

175
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:12,080
I've brought it.

176
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:13,440
Just take one glance, won't you?

177
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:14,280
Wang Meng.

178
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:19,200
Just do it for Lao Yang's sake.

179
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:21,920
Fine.

180
00:15:23,399 --> 00:15:24,480
For Lao Yang's sake.

181
00:15:24,755 --> 00:15:26,080
(Ancient silk manuscript's rubbing)

182
00:15:28,559 --> 00:15:29,399
Take a look.

183
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:32,600
It's a photocopy?

184
00:15:33,039 --> 00:15:35,240
You're no amateur.

185
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,440
Who carries real treasures

186
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:37,759
around the streets?

187
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:40,240
They'd crumble to dust.

188
00:15:41,639 --> 00:15:44,360
Besides, every trade has its own ways.

189
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,600
Your grandfather was too young

190
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:47,360
when he started tomb raiding,

191
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:48,840
which broke the rules.

192
00:15:59,639 --> 00:16:00,480
This thing

193
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:01,960
is well-preserved,

194
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:03,000
but

195
00:16:03,639 --> 00:16:04,479
it's a fake.

196
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:05,879
A fake?

197
00:16:06,519 --> 00:16:07,759
That can't be.

198
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:10,559
Anyway, I can't verify it.

199
00:16:10,559 --> 00:16:12,200
Go find another expert.

200
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:13,040
Wait.

201
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:17,960
Does this match
what your grandfather saw

202
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:19,000
back then?

203
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:19,919
Let me be honest.

204
00:16:19,919 --> 00:16:21,519
My grandfather was illiterate back then.

205
00:16:21,519 --> 00:16:23,000
He couldn't read this.

206
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,240
I can't tell you.

207
00:16:24,679 --> 00:16:25,639
What a coincidence.

208
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:28,360
Yes, indeed.

209
00:16:34,320 --> 00:16:36,320
Seems like there's really no hope left.

210
00:16:36,320 --> 00:16:37,279
Right.

211
00:16:39,519 --> 00:16:40,399
Got it.

212
00:16:42,679 --> 00:16:44,639
Collecting ancient texts
is complicated business.

213
00:16:44,799 --> 00:16:46,559
You shouldn't get too greedy.

214
00:16:47,360 --> 00:16:48,320
Young man,

215
00:16:48,519 --> 00:16:49,559
see you around.

216
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:50,879
See you around.

217
00:16:54,760 --> 00:16:55,600
I'm leaving.

218
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:56,440
See you.

219
00:17:19,080 --> 00:17:19,920
Wang Meng,

220
00:17:19,920 --> 00:17:20,760
the camera.

221
00:17:29,119 --> 00:17:29,960
You left something.

222
00:17:30,519 --> 00:17:32,160
Thank you.

223
00:17:32,759 --> 00:17:34,680
We'll meet again.

224
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:39,640
(Wushanju)
(Little did I know then)

225
00:17:40,599 --> 00:17:44,519
(that his appearance
would change my entire life.)

226
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:05,079
(This silk manuscript)

227
00:18:05,079 --> 00:18:06,839
(resembles the one
my grandfather had then.)

228
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:08,799
(I'm almost certain)

229
00:18:08,799 --> 00:18:10,240
(they're part of the same set.)

230
00:18:11,119 --> 00:18:12,440
(My gut tells me)

231
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:16,000
(Third Uncle)
(this silk manuscript holds secrets.)

232
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:17,920
(I plan to ask Third Uncle.)

233
00:18:18,919 --> 00:18:19,759
(In our family,)

234
00:18:19,759 --> 00:18:21,599
(only he inherited Grandpa's skills.)

235
00:18:22,039 --> 00:18:23,559
(In many ways,)

236
00:18:23,759 --> 00:18:25,480
(he's even better than Grandpa was.)

237
00:18:26,279 --> 00:18:28,160
(People outside call him Third Master.)

238
00:18:29,079 --> 00:18:30,440
(Due to business reasons,)

239
00:18:30,839 --> 00:18:33,640
(Third Uncle usually responds
to phone calls promptly.)

240
00:18:34,319 --> 00:18:35,720
(But there's always a day or two,)

241
00:18:36,279 --> 00:18:37,279
(like today,)

242
00:18:37,440 --> 00:18:38,960
(when he becomes totally unreachable,)

243
00:18:39,880 --> 00:18:41,559
(as if he's vanished.)

244
00:19:14,899 --> 00:19:16,113
(Wu Sanxing)

245
00:19:31,759 --> 00:19:32,720
(Third Uncle)
Nine o'clock.

246
00:19:32,720 --> 00:19:33,880
(Good stuff. Come quick.)
Chicken-eye yellow sand.

247
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:37,080
Dragon's Spine.

248
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:38,280
Come quick.

249
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:45,839
(Many years later,)

250
00:19:46,079 --> 00:19:47,240
(I would recall)

251
00:19:48,119 --> 00:19:49,400
(that from the moment I brought)

252
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:51,119
(the manuscript to Third Uncle,)

253
00:19:51,920 --> 00:19:53,279
(my life)

254
00:19:53,279 --> 00:19:55,480
(would undergo earth-shaking changes.)

255
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:55,960
Third Uncle,

256
00:20:55,960 --> 00:20:57,440
why didn't you wait for me?

257
00:20:58,160 --> 00:20:59,480
Your junk food's all ready.

258
00:20:59,480 --> 00:21:00,320
Hurry up.

259
00:21:00,519 --> 00:21:01,519
Can you eat now?

260
00:21:01,519 --> 00:21:02,880
You left me dinner,

261
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:04,119
not Dragon's Spine?

262
00:21:05,880 --> 00:21:06,839
Fine.

263
00:21:08,440 --> 00:21:09,720
It's not the first time anyway.

264
00:21:09,720 --> 00:21:10,960
You trick me every time.

265
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,319
To you,

266
00:21:13,319 --> 00:21:15,359
that thing is similar to Dragon's Spine.

267
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:17,839
There'll be new good stuff tomorrow.

268
00:21:17,839 --> 00:21:18,559
Eat first.

269
00:21:18,559 --> 00:21:19,359
Really?

270
00:21:19,359 --> 00:21:22,279
Tomorrow's stuff
will be three times better.

271
00:21:24,839 --> 00:21:25,759
Just eat your junk.

272
00:21:25,759 --> 00:21:26,799
Such a feast.

273
00:21:26,799 --> 00:21:27,759
I wonder

274
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:29,440
why anyone would eat the junk.

275
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:34,799
Third Uncle,

276
00:21:35,079 --> 00:21:37,240
why wouldn't you hold
that good stuff longer for me?

277
00:21:37,640 --> 00:21:38,559
What stuff?

278
00:21:39,160 --> 00:21:40,000
Dragon's Spine.

279
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:43,920
I took one look at its shape

280
00:21:44,279 --> 00:21:46,160
and knew roughly what was inside.

281
00:21:48,799 --> 00:21:50,759
An ancient weapon.

282
00:21:50,759 --> 00:21:51,599
Right?

283
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:56,960
But strangely enough,

284
00:21:57,319 --> 00:21:59,000
the person who bought Dragon's Spine

285
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:00,279
didn't look very old.

286
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:01,359
What's his background?

