Two people means a hundred kilos.

575
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:56,480
But

576
00:32:56,599 --> 00:32:58,559
I need two more team members.

577
00:32:59,079 --> 00:33:01,960
Four people
means two hundred kilos total.

578
00:33:02,240 --> 00:33:03,240
Who will you carry for?

579
00:33:03,880 --> 00:33:05,319
Will you carry mine?

580
00:33:05,759 --> 00:33:07,319
Your own gear too, right?

581
00:33:07,799 --> 00:33:09,119
Can you handle a hundred kilos?

582
00:33:09,400 --> 00:33:10,359
Enough.

583
00:33:11,519 --> 00:33:12,839
Just say you don't want me to go.

584
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:15,880
Fine, I'm leaving.

585
00:33:16,319 --> 00:33:17,480
My shop opens tomorrow.

586
00:33:17,839 --> 00:33:18,679
Bye.

587
00:33:32,480 --> 00:33:33,559
Leaving so soon?

588
00:33:38,599 --> 00:33:39,839
As a Wu,

589
00:33:39,920 --> 00:33:41,519
you gave up so easily?

590
00:33:42,920 --> 00:33:43,799
Seems like

591
00:33:44,119 --> 00:33:46,599
you didn't really want to go anyway.

592
00:33:48,519 --> 00:33:49,519
What do you mean?

593
00:33:51,119 --> 00:33:52,200
You'll take me?

594
00:33:55,839 --> 00:33:57,200
Your dad agreed.

595
00:33:59,519 --> 00:34:01,599
This is a search mission.

596
00:34:02,359 --> 00:34:03,920
He says it's relatively safe.

597
00:34:04,519 --> 00:34:05,960
I don't want our family's only heir

598
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:07,200
to miss out on adventuring.

599
00:34:08,079 --> 00:34:09,480
But this is the last time.

600
00:34:11,640 --> 00:34:13,000
Your coming with me

601
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:16,119
is better than your sneaking off alone.

602
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:18,360
Two things before departure.

603
00:34:19,159 --> 00:34:19,999
First,

604
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:21,440
crack the code.

605
00:34:21,719 --> 00:34:22,559
Second,

606
00:34:22,800 --> 00:34:24,199
recruit two more members.

607
00:34:45,599 --> 00:34:47,159
Got headshotted again.

608
00:34:47,159 --> 00:34:48,192
He sees through walls?

609
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:49,240
He's cheating?

610
00:34:49,639 --> 00:34:50,960
Who is it? Who's cheating?

611
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:53,239
That guy over there.

612
00:34:53,960 --> 00:34:56,159
Bro, that brat's definitely cheating.

613
00:34:56,280 --> 00:34:58,079
He's won ten rounds,
making us look idiotic!

614
00:34:58,840 --> 00:34:59,800
That brat.

615
00:35:09,679 --> 00:35:10,519
Buddy,

616
00:35:11,719 --> 00:35:12,639
having fun?

617
00:35:13,320 --> 00:35:14,320
You're a cheater, right?

618
00:35:16,440 --> 00:35:17,639
Say something!

619
00:35:18,440 --> 00:35:20,000
You think you're the boss here?

620
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:29,079
When someone talks to you,

621
00:35:29,079 --> 00:35:30,760
you should respond properly.

622
00:35:31,559 --> 00:35:33,559
Didn't your mother
teach you any manners?

623
00:35:35,719 --> 00:35:36,559
Stop looking at me!

624
00:35:56,679 --> 00:35:57,559
Your phone.

625
00:35:58,579 --> 00:36:00,352
(Wu Sanxing: Got a job. Come quick.)

626
00:36:03,731 --> 00:36:06,239
(Xingao Internet Cafe)

627
00:36:06,239 --> 00:36:07,079
How are you?

628
00:36:07,679 --> 00:36:08,519
Are you guys okay?

629
00:36:08,920 --> 00:36:09,760
Ma'am,

630
00:36:11,440 --> 00:36:12,760
don't cry.

631
00:36:12,960 --> 00:36:14,440
Hello, doctor.

632
00:36:14,559 --> 00:36:15,880
Thank you for your hard work.

633
00:36:20,880 --> 00:36:21,760
Wait.

634
00:36:21,920 --> 00:36:23,760
I wanted a 20 yuan discount
on the nursing fee.

635
00:36:23,760 --> 00:36:24,960
Is crying really necessary?

636
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:27,280
When doing business,

637
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:28,719
there's always some haggling.

638
00:36:31,400 --> 00:36:32,679
No 20-yuan discount anymore.

639
00:36:32,679 --> 00:36:33,400
Okay?

640
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:34,239
Okay?

641
00:36:34,239 --> 00:36:35,079
Stop crying.

642
00:36:35,199 --> 00:36:37,800
How about ten?

643
00:36:50,227 --> 00:36:55,744
(Third Master: Got a job. Come quick.)

644
00:36:56,920 --> 00:36:58,320
Stop crying.

645
00:36:58,960 --> 00:37:00,119
Stop it!

646
00:37:01,480 --> 00:37:02,960
I'll raise it by 20.

647
00:37:03,800 --> 00:37:04,880
50?

648
00:37:06,519 --> 00:37:07,760
Take good care of my mom.

649
00:37:07,800 --> 00:37:09,039
You have my word.

650
00:37:25,719 --> 00:37:27,360
(The helpers Third Uncle
found this time)

651
00:37:27,360 --> 00:37:28,280
(are familiar to me.)

652
00:37:29,760 --> 00:37:30,679
(This is Pan Zi,)

653
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:33,320
(Third Uncle's
longest-serving subordinate.)

654
00:37:34,760 --> 00:37:36,239
(When Third Uncle audits accounts,)

655
00:37:36,599 --> 00:37:37,800
(he always brings Pan Zi.)

656
00:37:38,199 --> 00:37:39,159
(With him present,)

657
00:37:39,480 --> 00:37:40,920
(no debt goes uncollected.)

658
00:37:41,719 --> 00:37:44,239
(In my memory,
anything Third Uncle demanded,)

659
00:37:44,519 --> 00:37:45,880
(he could always deliver.)

660
00:37:47,039 --> 00:37:48,159
(Though fierce to others)

661
00:37:48,599 --> 00:37:49,840
(and feared by everyone,)

662
00:37:50,239 --> 00:37:51,079
(he's kind to me.)

663
00:37:51,079 --> 00:37:51,960
Young Third Master.

664
00:37:51,960 --> 00:37:53,679
(He's taken me everywhere
since childhood.)

665
00:38:00,800 --> 00:38:01,719
(This is Da Kui.)

666
00:38:01,920 --> 00:38:03,079
(His strength is legendary.)

667
00:38:03,400 --> 00:38:05,000
(He can kill an ox with one punch.)

668
00:38:07,480 --> 00:38:09,000
(He operates without principles.)

669
00:38:09,920 --> 00:38:11,280
(Except toward Third Uncle,)

670
00:38:11,760 --> 00:38:13,360
(for others, payment alone)

671
00:38:13,360 --> 00:38:15,000
(can make him work against allies.)

672
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:16,320
(He's even double-dealing.)

673
00:38:17,159 --> 00:38:19,719
(I never trusted his integrity.)

674
00:38:19,719 --> 00:38:20,719
(Until he retorted,)

675
00:38:21,119 --> 00:38:23,639
("Can integrity save my mother's life?")

676
00:38:23,759 --> 00:38:24,599
(That's when I knew)

677
00:38:24,599 --> 00:38:26,079
(his mother was critically ill)

678
00:38:26,800 --> 00:38:28,159
(and he needed a lot of money.)

679
00:38:28,280 --> 00:38:29,120
Hello.

680
00:38:29,679 --> 00:38:30,519
Third Master.

681
00:38:30,519 --> 00:38:31,480
Sharper than ever.

682
00:38:31,480 --> 00:38:32,760
- Third Master.
- Bulked up.

683
00:38:32,760 --> 00:38:33,679
I got a new liquor.

684
00:38:33,800 --> 00:38:34,640
We'll try it later.

685
00:38:34,960 --> 00:38:36,800
This time we're retrieving one person.

686
00:38:37,039 --> 00:38:38,440
The client's paying eight million.

687
00:38:38,639 --> 00:38:39,760
We'll split it.

688
00:38:42,159 --> 00:38:43,440
But here's the thing.

689
00:38:43,440 --> 00:38:45,079
About where we're going,

690
00:38:45,800 --> 00:38:46,800
I don't know yet.

691
00:38:46,920 --> 00:38:49,840
First, we need to decipher this map.

692
00:38:52,499 --> 00:38:56,156
(Ancient silk manuscript's rubbing)

693
00:39:10,320 --> 00:39:11,880
(Kulou 10.)

694
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:13,079
(Zhu 8.)

695
00:39:13,280 --> 00:39:14,800
(Beihe 1?)

696
00:39:14,800 --> 00:39:15,639
Any progress?

697
00:39:15,639 --> 00:39:16,479
Got it.

698
00:39:17,079 --> 00:39:19,880
(These symbols form
an ancient Lu State terrain map.)

699
00:39:21,320 --> 00:39:22,239
(Refine further.)

700
00:39:24,280 --> 00:39:25,159
(Jiuqi 2.)

701
00:39:25,519 --> 00:39:26,639
(Tianlao...)

702
00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:28,920
(Sangong 1.)

703
00:39:29,159 --> 00:39:30,400
(And five fuxi stars.)

704
00:39:38,239 --> 00:39:39,239
Let me see.

705
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:43,800
It matches.

706
00:39:44,159 --> 00:39:46,760
(It's Quling County
within ancient Lu territory.)

707
00:39:52,199 --> 00:39:53,039
Young Third Master,

708
00:39:53,199 --> 00:39:54,239
let me look again.

709
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:56,600
This?

710
00:39:56,679 --> 00:39:57,519
Right.

711
00:39:58,359 --> 00:39:59,199
Look.

712
00:39:59,199 --> 00:40:01,519
(The place called Hechuan in Quling.)

713
00:40:02,119 --> 00:40:03,440
It looks like the star map.

714
00:40:12,079 --> 00:40:13,079
Right.

715
00:40:13,400 --> 00:40:15,039
There's hope.

716
00:40:15,920 --> 00:40:17,519
Come on.

717
00:40:21,679 --> 00:40:23,840
(Hechuan corresponds
to present-day Pengzhou.)

718
00:40:24,880 --> 00:40:25,920
(We're almost there.)

719
00:40:26,119 --> 00:40:28,119
(This shows mountain ranges.)

720
00:40:28,719 --> 00:40:30,079
(This depicts rivers.)

721
00:40:31,199 --> 00:40:32,559
(Stack them all together.)

722
00:40:37,880 --> 00:40:38,760
A bit over here.

723
00:40:42,519 --> 00:40:43,400
(They match.)

724
00:40:43,400 --> 00:40:45,840
(The map's center points
to an underground cave.)

725
00:40:52,400 --> 00:40:53,480
Let's go to Pengzhou first.

726
00:40:53,840 --> 00:40:54,680
(We leave tomorrow.)

727
00:41:01,079 --> 00:41:03,079
(We drank heavily that night.)

728
00:41:03,559 --> 00:41:05,239
(I was in a daze.)

729
00:41:05,239 --> 00:41:07,280
(Everything felt surreal.)

730
00:41:09,760 --> 00:41:12,119
(I thought I'd seized this opportunity.)

731
00:41:12,800 --> 00:41:14,159
(Am I right, Grandpa?)

732
00:41:28,199 --> 00:41:29,440
Grandpa?

733
00:42:17,604 --> 00:42:20,467
♪O light, who lights the candle
to illuminate♪

734
00:42:20,745 --> 00:42:23,743
♪The riddles time has devised♪

735
00:42:24,031 --> 00:42:28,230
♪O light, you shift the balance
of light and dark♪

736
00:42:28,684 --> 00:42:30,294
♪Flowing unrestrained♪

737
00:42:30,481 --> 00:42:33,213
♪Behold, the ground where someone stood♪

738
00:42:33,530 --> 00:42:36,383
♪The chessboard
lies riddled with wounds♪

739
00:42:36,721 --> 00:42:39,540
♪Behold, the truest lies
before our eyes♪

740
00:42:39,795 --> 00:42:42,549
♪What does falseness matter?♪

741
00:42:42,694 --> 00:42:45,977
♪With hearts ablaze and unyielding,
we march toward♪

742
00:42:46,295 --> 00:42:48,876
♪The most forgiving execution ground♪

743
00:42:49,109 --> 00:42:54,693
♪All shattered fragments echo hollowly♪

744
00:42:55,463 --> 00:42:58,832
♪In the end, we find solace
in the lingering sunset♪

745
00:42:58,928 --> 00:43:01,574
♪That still clings to our skin♪

746
00:43:01,852 --> 00:43:07,382
♪No time to tell our tempestuous tale♪

747
00:43:07,749 --> 00:43:10,586
♪The most towering peaks♪

748
00:43:10,838 --> 00:43:13,783
♪Have witnessed our wild defiance♪

749
00:43:14,118 --> 00:43:16,921
♪Moonlight of full moons above the sea♪

750
00:43:17,113 --> 00:43:19,898
♪Is poured into our cups♪

751
00:43:20,275 --> 00:43:23,197
♪The most aloof snow-capped mountains♪

752
00:43:23,434 --> 00:43:26,452
♪Have quietly heard our chants♪

753
00:43:26,715 --> 00:43:29,628
♪Marvelled by all, our story's twists♪

754
00:43:29,648 --> 00:43:32,905
♪Are commonplace to us♪

755
00:43:46,642 --> 00:43:49,468
♪O light, you trace
perilous paths behind♪

756
00:43:49,806 --> 00:43:52,712
♪Yet illuminate smooth roads ahead♪

757
00:43:53,028 --> 00:43:57,171
♪O light, you mend this flawed world♪

758
00:43:57,710 --> 00:43:59,024
♪Without measure♪

759
00:43:59,184 --> 00:44:02,322
♪Behold the uncertainties
you've calculated♪

760
00:44:02,637 --> 00:44:05,505
♪And the hesitation you arrived with♪

761
00:44:05,803 --> 00:44:08,649
♪Behold, at last, courage stands alone♪

762
00:44:08,882 --> 00:44:11,546
♪Against life's absurdity♪

763
00:44:11,766 --> 00:44:15,184
♪With hearts ablaze and unyielding,
we march toward♪

764
00:44:15,184 --> 00:44:17,704
♪The most forgiving execution ground♪

765
00:44:18,083 --> 00:44:21,259
♪All shattered fragments echo hollowly♪

